    "overall_strategy": "We integrate three literature-supported routes: (1) the cyanosulfidic photoredox pathway (Sutherland et al.) in surface settings to build the five-carbon nitrile core, cyclize and hydrolyze to proline; (2) a classical Strecker approach from 4-aminobutanal under wet-dry and UV cycles on clays; and (3) a metabolism-first hydrothermal route via pyruvate/glyoxylate to \u03b1-ketoglutarate, transamination to glutamate, cyclization to P5C and reduction to proline. Cross-environment links shuttle key hubs (P5C, 4-aminobutanal, pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile) between vents and pools, enabling 10 convergent pathways to the target.",
